esponding-hiv-christian-ministers-pastors-and-communities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "A Pacific Guide on Responding to HIV for Christian Ministers, Pastors and Communities", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/pacific-guide-responding-hiv-christian-ministers-pastors-and-communities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "265f60bac6b956af49961d8b86b51185e77be98d7d4ddbe0ba6e57e572ce0e45"}}, "hash": "265f60bac6b956af49961d8b86b51185e77be98d7d4ddbe0ba6e57e572ce0e45", "text": "said to those standing by, \u2018Take his mina away from him and give it to the one who has ten minas.\u2019 25 \u201c \u2018Sir,\u2019 they said, \u2018he already has ten!\u2019 26 \u201cHe replied, \u2018I tell you that to everyone who has, more will be given, but as for the one who has nothing, even what he has will be taken away.(Luke 19: 11-26) The trauma upon knowing of infection Many people discover that they are infected with HIV by \u201caccident\u201d, when they are proposed to conduct a blood test, for example as an expecting mother or as a blood donor; they have no idea that they are infected. \u2022 It could be that none of the symptoms had appeared yet. \u2022 It could be that they have not engaged in risky behaviours (for example in the case of a faithful wife infected by her unfaithful husband) \u2022 This discovery results in a trauma for many people. \u2022 The Bible still proclaims God\u2019s love, grace, and power to them. \u2022 This message is addressed to those who undergo this trauma. A message to people living with HIV Disease and predicaments are invitations for courage and faith 28 And we know that in all things God works for the good of those who love him, who have been called according to his purpose. (Romans 8: 28) 2 Consider it pure joy, my brothers, whenever you face trials of many kinds, 3 because you know that the testing of your faith develops perseverance. (James 1: 2-3) 13 When tempted, no one should say, \u201cGod is tempting me.\u201d For God cannot be tempted by evil, nor does he tempt anyone; (James 1: 13) \u2022 Disease, predicaments and tribulations are all a test of faith. \u2022 The raging war that befalls us calls our souls to seek purity in faith. \u2022 Long-suffering and perseverance result in spontaneous joy and simple faith in the souls that pass the test. \u2022 A person who undergoes hardships is not judged in the same measure as one whose life has been easy going. You are created in the image of God; and God loves you whether you are responsible for your condition or not; He wishes to work out wonders in your life. God has a wonderful purpose for every moment in our lives; He has good works and He hath before ordained that we should walk in them. We - all humans- are His handmaiden, the very theme of His concern and love. His capable hands wish to intervene in our toughest circumstances, to do the good works in which we are ordained to walk. None of us knows when we shall die; every moment that we live is but a gift from God, an invitation to be fruitful and to live a life that reflects His glory. Changing our lives daily into the likeness of His love is a vocation for all mankind. The gravely ailing, or those anticipating suffering, are not exempted. God calls upon you not to fall into the ordeal of wondering whether your condition is a reflection of His punishment and wrath; whether you are guilty; whether others are guilty, or whether you are innocent and that therefore God deserves your anger and bitterness. The Lord invites you to ask the essential questions in life: How can I live a fruitful and meaningful life? How can I recognize the presence of the Lord within my ordeal or tribulation? How can I be sure of the steadfastness of my relationship with the Lord; or that I\u2019m being edified in His grace, His love and His service? How can I enjoy every single day of my life in a joyful relationship with Him \u2013 ministering for Him and to others? Whether you think you are responsible for acquiring HIV through carelessness or not, you need to be sure of God\u2019s forgiveness for your sins, and that you abide in Him; for whosoever abides in Him will never be lost, but will have eternal life. So pray a prayer of simple faith asking the Lord to enter into your life, to fill it with His grace and love; to give you the assurance that you are His son or daughter, and that no one will ever be able to snatch you from His hand. Guideline for Christian Leaders Guideline for Christian Leaders 22 23 \u2022 The Lord calls upon us to accept in faith and embrace the struggles placed before us, that we might be victorious in our hardships, and that our victory might bring forth heavenly glories and tangible fruits on earth. \u2022", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ebd60320-384a-4ad8-b084-0e3c4f0a3254": {"__data__": {"id_": "ebd60320-384a-4ad8-b084-0e3c4f0a3254", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/pacific-guide-responding-hiv-christian-ministers-pastors-and-communities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "A Pacific Guide on Responding to HIV for Christian Ministers, Pastors and Communities", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/pacific-guide-responding-hiv-christian-ministers-pastors-and-communities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "cce2448ca85f9305153a3e0c0ea4a389a43dc8942bee0d787234d847699ba2b0"}}, "hash": "cce2448ca85f9305153a3e0c0ea4a389a43dc8942bee0d787234d847699ba2b0", "text": "People living with HIV are able, through the hope, faith and love that they demonstrate, to pass on a message of power and joy to a needy world. \u2022 Yet, you need to accept the love and power that this requires. Such power does not exist in seclusion, anger or bitterness; rather, it comes from loving God and those around us. How to gain spiritual and emotional power 3 Join a support group or be ready to form a support group for people living with HIV. The power you will experience in such a group is capable of supporting you in moments of despair, weakness or fear. 3 Cast yourself into the hands of the Mighty God who can do all things: He can heal you, sustain you when facing a crisis, grant you new faith to share with others, and make you a source of faith, joy and love to many others. 3 The way you cope with your condition could bring about incredible glory to God. 3 Your care not to transmit the virus to others, awareness of your condition, concern for your treatment, nutrition, and a healthy lifestyle, all this along with your prayers for yourself will bring glory to God before Man, angels and the entire universe. Lesson Three: A message of love and hope for people living with AIDS Themes: Christ identified with your suffering and ailment. Nothing can separate us from the love of Christ. Life is measured not by the number of days lived, but rather the depth lived. Faith gives a meaning to life. Care for the body and the spirit. Sione\u2019s story Sione learnt he had HIV three years ago and began ARV treatment. He began to feel and look better. But then the stories started. \u201cThe rumours started to circulate that there was a Tokelauan guy in Samoa who had this AIDS. The rumours were from other Tokelau Islanders here.\u201d Sione felt embarrassed and stigmatised. \u201cOne day, I went to my office and I asked someone from my island if there was any story about me back home. He said yes. I asked him what kind of story? He told me he\u2019d heard that I got AIDS. At that time, I didn\u2019t know what I would do because people were talking about me.\u201d Worse was to come. \u201cI walked into my office one day, you know I\u2019m a hard worker and do very well in my job. But my boss called me in and told me: \u2018Sorry, there is no more job for you.\u2019 I asked him why and he said: \u2018Because there is a virus in your body, you cannot work anymore\u2019.\u201d Sione was fortunate in the support of his wife and both their families. He now has his own small business and describes himself as having no problems. \u2018I\u2019m very happy to talk to people, not to talk about the disease, but just socialise and interact with people and my family,\u201d he says. Asked if he plans to publicly disclose his status and do advocacy work, Sione laughs \u201cNo that\u2019s not for me. I am a weak person, but who knows, maybe later\u201d. Source: Renagi Taukarai, PIAF Christ identified with your suffering and ailment 4 Surely he took up our infirmities and carried our sorrows, yet we considered him stricken by God, smitten by him, and afflicted. 5 But he was pierced for our transgressions, he was crushed for our iniquities; the punishment that brought us peace was upon him, and by his wounds we are healed. 6 We all, like sheep, have gone astray, each of us has turned to his own way; and the LORD has laid on him the iniquity of us all. 7 He was oppressed and afflicted, yet he did not open his mouth; he was led like a lamb to the slaughter, and as a sheep before her shearers is silent, so he did not open his mouth. 8 By oppression and judgment he was taken away. And who can speak of his descendants? For he was cut off from the land of the living; for the transgression of my people he was stricken. 9 He was assigned a grave with the wicked, and with the rich in his death, though Guideline for Christian Leaders Guideline for Christian Leaders 24 25 he had done no violence, nor was any deceit in his mouth. 10 Yet it was the LORD\u2019s will to crush him and cause him to suffer, and though the LORD makes his life a guilt offering, he will see his offspring and prolong his days, and the will", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "f0f93df8-740a-4dbb-867f-45bfbcadd58b": {"__data__": {"id_": "f0f93df8-740a-4dbb-867f-45bfbcadd58b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/pacific-guide-responding-hiv-christian-ministers-pastors-and-communities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "A Pacific Guide on Responding to HIV for Christian Ministers, Pastors and Communities", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/pacific-guide-responding-hiv-christian-ministers-pastors-and-communities", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "c9e6a083bf475d64e5b400f5531a5a2b6cf6a288883964774a35de15728460c2"}}, "hash": "c9e6a083bf475d64e5b400f5531a5a2b6cf6a288883964774a35de15728460c2", "text": "of the LORD will prosper in his hand. 11 After the suffering of his soul, he will see the light of life and be satisfied; by his knowledge my righteous servant will justify many, and he will bear their iniquities. (Isaiah 53: 4-11) 9 In all their distress he too was distressed, and the angel of his presence saved them. In his love and mercy he redeemed them; he lifted them up and carried them all the days of old. (Isaiah 63: 9) 15 For we do not have a high priest who is unable to sympathize with our weaknesses, but we have one who has been tempted in every way, just as we are--yet was without sin. 16 Let us then approach the throne of grace with confidence, so that we may receive mercy and find grace to help us in our time of need.(Hebrews 4: 14-16) \u2022 Christ, our great high priest, suffered for the sake of each one of us. \u2022 He intercedes for us to grant us power to face suffering. \u2022 The Lord identifies with our weaknesses, impairments and infirmities and gives us power, might, health and life. \u2022 People believed that Jesus suffered because God was punishing him, as Isaiah says, but in fact His suffering was to deliver us from our sins. \u2022 People living with HIV suffer because of their condition, and because of people\u2019s insensitivity towards them. \u2022 Yet, God is aware and is mindful of our suffering; He personally suffered like us. He feels the pain of our infirmities and is mindful of the injustice befalling us; He too was wounded and unfairly treated unto death. \u2022 Indeed, He was wounded to give us life. He died and was resurrected that we may be restored to life along with Him. He lived out pain that we may face it with courage and power. He was unjustly treated to give us mercy and justice; to carry our sins and inequities. \u2022 Let us trust Him, the Mighty One, who is able to heal our bodies, and raise both bodies and spirits to eternal life, where there is no death, disease, sorrow or injustice. Nothing can separate us from the love of Christ 37 No, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him who loved us. 38 For I am convinced that neither death nor life, neither angels nor demons, neither the present nor the future, nor any powers, 39 neither height nor depth, nor anything else in all creation, will be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.(Romans 8: 37-39). \u2022 There is no tribulation or disease upon earth that is able to deprive us or separate us from the love of Christ. \u2022 The Lord loves you, even as you are ailing, weak and fainting; He longs to hear your voice, and to listen to the beat of your heart, full of His love, closeness and trust in His blessed person. \u2022 Ask Him to dwell in your heart and to fill your life with His spirit. \u2022 Trust His blood with forgiveness of sins and pursue the sacraments with faith and joy; He will give you power to face death and life - life as you live it and life after death. \u2022 The early Christians trusted Christ despite persecution, tribulation, famines (hunger), disgrace (nakedness), danger and death. \u2022 Every moment that you have on earth is an opportunity to experience and live such love and such trust. \u2022 Who can separate us from the love of Christ? Indeed nothing can separate us from Christ; and nothing can separate us from His love for us. Life is measured not by the number of days lived, but rather the depth lived 8 For it is by grace you have been saved, through faith--and this not from yourselves, it is the gift of God-- (Ephesians 2: 8) \u2022 By grace, Christ has bestowed upon us the amazing salvation that we receive by faith and trust in His work. \u2022 Every day that we live along with him by faith provides a glimpse of the everlasting life that we are to live with Him as we see Him face to face. \u2022 Such salvation is not contingent on your deeds, goodness or righteousness; but rather on His goodness and His righteousness. \u2022 Jesus Christ lived here on earth only for 33 years, yet His life changed the course of history and the face of the entire universe. \u2022 Life is not measured by the number of years lived,", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_se