king at the OVC households first, the impact of the food sup- port program is clearly seen as the intervention households spend a much lower percentage of expen- ditures on food (t=6.0, p<.00). In- terestingly, they also pay a lower percentage on medical costs (t=2.5, p=.01); since no additional medical services are provided as part of the program, this can be presumed to be a result of better health status due to improved food security. Comparing the control and inter- vention households, it is seen that the intervention households gen- erally spend the money they save on", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "597ce267-8903-4b8e-87f9-59d491f2e6ba": {"__data__": {"id_": "597ce267-8903-4b8e-87f9-59d491f2e6ba", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/preliminary-study-impact-hiv-poverty-and-food-security-among-hiv-affected-households-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "A Preliminary Study of the Impact of HIV on Poverty and Food Security Among HIV-affected Households in Asia", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/preliminary-study-impact-hiv-poverty-and-food-security-among-hiv-affected-households-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "92f71a1f40c044647ca4a7f9f5b38b0b92f9ebae4637b0f6d9110561c8331188"}, "3": {"node_id": "c01220b8-438e-4a66-b585-ccb4e135e3d2", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/preliminary-study-impact-hiv-poverty-and-food-security-among-hiv-affected-househ